<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Culkin, Wife Call It Quits  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ''Home Alone'' star Macaulay Culkin and his
actress wife of two years have separated.
</P>
<P>
   ''Macaulay Culkin and his wife Rachel Miner have temporarily
separated,'' the actor's publicist, Paul Bloch, said Sunday. ''It
is very amicable, and they remain the best of friends.''
</P>
<P>
   Culkin, 20, and Miner, 19, met at New York's Professional
Children's School and wed on June 21, 1998, when both were age 17.
</P>
<P>
   Miner has appeared on Broadway in ''The Diary of Anne Frank''
and in the soap opera ''The Guiding Light.'' Culkin's other film
credits include ''My Girl,'' ''Home Alone 2: Lost in New York,''
''The Good Son,'' and ''Richie Rich.''
</P>
</TEXT>
