<HEADLINE> 15-year-old girl found dead, high school classmate charged with murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WATKINS GLEN, N.Y. (AP) - A 16-year-old high school student was
charged with second-degree murder on Monday, only hours after the
body of one of his classmates was discovered at the edge of Seneca
Lake.
</P>
<P>
   Joshua Horein, 16, of Watkins Glen, was arrested Monday in
connection with the death of Amber Brockway, also a village
resident. He was arraigned in Town of Dix Justice Court and was
being held without bail at Schuyler County Jail.
</P>
<P>
   Brockway's body was found in a remote area near the southern
edge of the lake, according to the Schuyler County Sheriff's
Department. An autopsy performed by the Monroe County Medical
Examiner's Office indicated that she died immediately after being
struck several times in the head with a blunt object.
</P>
<P>
   Family members had reported Amber missing Saturday evening after
she failed to return home, and police began an around-the-clock
search for her. She was last seen at approximately 7 p.m. near the
Watkins Glen public fishing pier, where she had walked to meet with
some friends, investigators said.
</P>
<P>
   No motive was given for the murder, but investigators confirmed
that Amber and her attacker had been friends and that both attended
Watkins Glen High School. No further arrests were expected, police
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
