Commercial Township, where she was found by the New Jersey State
Police.
</P>
<P>
   ''She reported being sexually assaulted in an isolated area,''
Wilent said in a prepared statement released late Tuesday by
police. Wilent could not be reached for comment Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
   The girl, whose identity was withheld by police, was treated and
released at Burdette Tomlin Hospital in Cape May Court House.
</P>
