<HEADLINE> Rangers Recall Pitcher Cubillan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND (AP) -- Darwin Cubillan, a right-hander acquired last
month in a trade with Toronto, was recalled from Triple-A Oklahoma
on Monday by the Texas Rangers, who optioned reliever Francisco
Cordero back to the minors/
</P>
<P>
   ubillan, 25, came to Texas in a July 19 deal with the Blue Jays
along with infielder Mike Young. In six games at Oklahoma, Cubillan
did not allow a run in 13 innings, got one save and struck out 10.
</P>
<P>
   ''What he has done at Triple-A has been exciting,'' Rangers
manager Johnny Oates said of Cubillan, who spent seven seasons in
the Yankees organization before signing with Toronto as a free
agent in November.
</P>
<P>
   Cordero, 22, went 1-1 with a 5.62 ERA in 41 games for the
Rangers. He got off to a good start this season, but he allowed
runs in five of his last six appearances.
</P>
<P>
   ''He can get big league hitters out right now, but I think he
has a chance to be a superstar out of the bullpen,'' Oates said.
''He's got the arm for it. He's got the slider for it, but
location-wise he's got to get better.''
</P>
</TEXT>
