<HEADLINE> Vikings' Moss Shows No Ill Effects  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANKATO, Minn. (AP) -- Minnesota Vikings receiver Randy Moss was
back on the practice field Monday, going through a full workout and
showing no effects from a bruised shoulder and ribs.
</P>
<P>
   ''Randy's a very tough player,'' coach Dennis Green said. ''He
and Cris (Carter) have great work habits.''
</P>
<P>
   Moss was injured on a spectacular 55-yard catch and run in the
second quarter of Saturday's 25-24 preseason loss to the New
Orleans Saints. He landed on his shoulder after hurdling a defender
inside the 5-yard line.
</P>
<P>
   Moss wore extra padding around his ribs during Monday's workout.
</P>
