<HEADLINE> Travis Butler in custody of dead mother's friend  </HEADLINE>
By PAUL PAYNE
<TEXT>
<P>
   JACKSON, Miss. (AP) - Deputies removed 10-year-old Travis Butler
from his grandparents' custody and placed him with the woman who
discovered him living with his mother's corpse, friends and
relatives said.
</P>
<P>
   Dorothy Jeffries, who found Travis in a Memphis, Tenn.,
apartment in December, took custody of the boy in her Olive Branch
home Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Travis had been living with his grandparents in a single-wide
trailer in rural Carthage, but after a custody hearing last week
with Chancery Judge Bill Lutz, he was moved.
</P>
<P>
   ''I raised the boy most his life,'' said H.P. Wilder, Travis'
step-grandfather. ''I couldn't understand why they want to give him
to this strange person.''
</P>
<P>
   Last fall, Travis lived for a month with his dead mother, too
afraid to tell anyone because he feared being placed in foster
care. His mother, Crystal Wells, died Nov. 3 from a lung tumor.
</P>
<P>
   Travis cut his hair, fixed meals and went to school every day
from the time his mother died until her body was discovered by
Wells' friend.
</P>
<P>
   Jeffries could not immediately be reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   After the ordeal, Travis' maternal grandmother, Shirley Wilder,
assumed custody.
</P>
<P>
   H.P. Wilder said Leake County deputies picked up Travis and
drove him to the Jeffries' home in north Mississippi.
</P>
<P>
   ''He didn't want to go,'' Wilder said. ''She wasn't no friend of
Crystal's.''
</P>
<P>
   Travis' plight has gained national attention and amassed
hundreds of thousands of dollars in donations. He appeared on the
Montel Williams show and trust accounts have been established in
his name.
</P>
<P>
   Betsy Rathe, a New York City production company owner who
started an education fund worth nearly $100,000, said ''he's in
good hands.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I spoke to Travis today and he seemed OK,'' Rathe told The
Associated Press on Monday. ''All I care about is that he grows and
thrives. Whether it is with the Jeffries or not doesn't matter.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
