<HEADLINE> Cops: Cop in Video Shot by Officer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- An officer whose gunshot wound to the thumb
led to a frantic police chase and a nationally televised police
beating of the suspect was actually shot by another officer,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Charges of attempted murder and aggravated assault against
suspect Thomas Jones were dropped Monday after ballistics tests
indicated he did not shoot Officer Michael Livewell July 12. Jones
is still accused of carjacking, robbery and fleeing police.
</P>
<P>
   Philadelphia District Attorney Lynne M. Abraham said the shot
was fired by Officer Cedric Gaines as he and Livewell struggled
with Jones.
</P>
<P>
   ''My client has always maintained he didn't have a gun,'' said
Jones' attorney, Blake Berenbaum.
</P>
<P>
   Jones, 30, was initially pulled over by police for allegedly
driving a stolen car. He then drove off in a police vehicle. Later,
a television helicopter videotaped officers kicking and punching
him during his arrest.
</P>
<P>
   Jones, who had been in critical condition, was released from a
hospital Monday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
