<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SkyChiefs 2, Red Sox 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   Syracuse, N.Y. (AP) -- Joey Hamilton tossed a complete game and
Kevin Witt hit a two-run homer for the Syracuse SkyChiefs in a 2-1
win over the Pawtucket Red Sox Monday in the International League.
</P>
<P>
   Hamilton (2-2) and Carlos Castillo (1-2) throwing for Pawtucket
had a dual no-hitter through 6 1/2 innings.
</P>
<P>
   The no-hitter ended in the eighth. Freddy Garcia had a leadoff
single to left. Jim Chamblee pitch-ran for Garcia and with one out
the shutout came to an end. Lou Merloni doubled to center scoring
Chamblee.
</P>
<P>
   Ryan Freel broke up the no-hitter with a double to the gap in
left. With one out Witt crushed the ball to deep right. Castillo
also surrendered a double to Andy Thompson later in the inning.
</P>
<P>
   Castillo was relieved by Tim Young in the eighth.
</P>
<P>
   Castillo was put into a starting role because Pawtucket had to
shake up its rotation after Bret Saberhagen's short six pitch
outing on Saturday which required Sunday's starter Sun-Woo Kim to
enter the game. Subsequently Monday's starter Dan Smith went to the
hill on Sunday leaving no rested arms for the Red Sox.
</P>
<P>
   Syracuse has won eight of its last nine while Pawtucket has won
only one of its last nine.
</P>
</TEXT>
