<HEADLINE> Phila. Protest Bail Reduced  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- A judge on Monday reduced bail for a protest
organizer to $100,000 from $1 million, a figure many attorneys had
called ''ridiculous.''
</P>
<P>
   John Sellers, 33, director of the Berkeley, Calif.-based Ruckus
Society, is charged with misdemeanors for allegedly orchestrating
property damage during protests at the recent Republican National
Convention.
</P>
<P>
   Co-defendant Terrence McGuckin's bail hearing was postponed
until Tuesday. McGuckin, being held on $450,000 bail, is a leader
of Philadelphia ACT UP, the largest chapter of the national AIDS
advocacy group.
</P>
</TEXT>
