<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-07 23:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Plaza Hotel security guards exchange shots with burglary suspect  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - An altercation between security guards and a
burglary suspect in the lobby of the Plaza Hotel turned into a wild
chase and shootout Monday night, ending with police arresting the
wounded suspect down the street from the Edwardian-style Central
Park south landmark.
</P>
<P>
   The suspect, who was not identified, was approached in the lobby
by hotel security about 9 p.m., police said.
</P>
<P>
   As he left the hotel, he pulled a gun and fired shots at the
guards, prompting one of them to fire one shot back, hitting the
suspect in the arm, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Witnesses described a wild scene as the fleeing suspect, wearing
a navy suit and tie, skirted around the William Tecumseh Sherman
statue in front of the hotel and hopped into a taxi at 60th Street
and Fifth Avenue, a block away.
</P>
<P>
   Police cars hemmed the taxi in. The suspect jumped out of the
cab and was wrestled to the ground by police officers, said one
witness, limousine driver Diego Morales, 43.
</P>
<P>
   Fifth Avenue was closed between 60th and 62nd streets for about
two hours while police interviewed witnesses and combed the area
for shell casings.
</P>
<P>
   The suspect was taken to St. Clair's Hospital, where he was
listed in stable condition.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
